Lena Pappenheim, Respondent v. The Metropolitan Elevated Railway Company, et al., Appellants. Decided January 5, 1891. Appeal from judgment" entered upon the decision of a judge at the equity term. Davies & Rapallo, for appellants. Sackett & Bennett, for respondent.

Before Freedman and Ingraham, JJ.

Per Curiam.

The judgment should be affirmed, with costs.
